  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="septet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">Carves very ill, yet will palm all the Meats:</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">He Eats more than Six; and Drinks more than he Eats.</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">Four Pipes after Dinner he constantly smokes;</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">And seasons his Whifs with impertinent Jokes.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">Yet sighing, he says, We must certainly break;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">And my cruel Unkindness compells him to speak:</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="11">For of late I invite Him â€” but Four Times a Week.</l>
    </lg>
